The paper deals with the Max-Cut problem, which is a well-known problem in graph theory and optimization. The algorithm proposed in the paper is parameterized by the number of crossings in a given drawing of the graph, which suggests that it may be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph drawing (cs.GT). The paper also mentions that the Max-Cut problem is NP-hard, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper proposes a fixed-parameter tractable algorithm, which is a topic often studied in parameterized complexity (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
